The Lagos State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has commended the state governor, Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu for approving N35,000 as the new minimum wage for workers in the state. Lagos APC in a statement issued at the weekend by its Assistant Publicity Secretary, Mr. Abiodun Salami, said the approval of the new wage by Governor Sanwo-Olu showed that the APC -led state government is a caring government. He said it was unprecedented that workers in the state will be getting a higher wage than those of the Federal Government, describing Governor Sanwo-Olu as lover of workers .   He said the new minimum wage was another testimony that the APC government is committed to serving Lagosians, saying the Sanwo-Olu administration had achieved remarkable achievements since inception . His words: ‘’We commend Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu for the approval of the N35,000 minimum wage for workers, which is higher that the wage of Federal government .  ‘’During the campaign, Sanwo-Olu promised to impact of the lives of the people through impactful policies, programmes and projects. He has been fulfilling the promises from the first day he assumed office and the new minimum wage is a sign that more dividends of democracy are coming for Lagosians .   ‘’We urge residents to continue to support the APC-led state government in its unflinching commitment to take the state to greater heights.” Salami also urged residents to keep faith with APC as it is the only party with programmes to promote development.